ot gentext?><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">Guitars come in a wide variety of shapes, sizes, and configurations, but they have         certain features in common.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref><topicref is-chapter="true" class="- map/topicref " href="#unique_6" toc="yes" type="concept"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="concept_qbf_phx_nrb"><resourceid appid="concept_qbf_phx_nrb" class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic"/><navtitle href="#unique_6" class="- topic/navtitle ">Drop-D Tuning</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">Drop-D tuning involves tuning the low E string (E2) and high E string (E4) a whole         tone lower to low D (D2) and high D (D4) respectively. This allows easier playing of         specific chords.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref><topicref is-chapter="true" class="- map/topicref " href="#unique_7" toc="yes" type="concept"><topicmeta class="- map/topicmeta " data-topic-id="drop-c"><resourceid appid="drop-c" class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic"/><navtitle href="#unique_7" class="- topic/navtitle ">Drop-C Tuning</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">Drop-C tuning involves tuning the low E string (E2, string six) and high E string (E4, string one) two whole         tones lower to low C (C2) and high C (C4) respectively. This allows easier playing of         specific chords.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topicref>

