<title class="- topic/title "><ph class="- topic/ph topic/title-wrapper ">How to Tune an Acoustic Guitar</ph></title>
<taskbody class="- topic/body  task/taskbody ">
     <prereq class="- topic/section  task/prereq " id="unique_1_Connect_42_prereq_lr4_dvn_mrb" nd:nd-id="prereq_lr4_dvn_mrb">This tutorial is for standard tuning of a guitar. </prereq>
     <context class="- topic/section  task/context "><p class="- topic/p ">You will first need to see if your guitar has tuning pegs on the left and the right side of the headstock or just on the left side. <xref class="- topic/xref " href="#unique_2" type="reference"><?ditaot usertext?>
                See this reference about guitar basics<?ditaot genshortdesc?><desc class="- topic/desc ">Guitars come in a wide variety of shapes, sizes, and configurations, but they have         certain features in common.</desc></xref>.</p><image class="- topic/image " height="400" href="file:/Users/scottmcmahan/Desktop/techwritingsamples/guitar/guitar_headstocks.jpg" id="unique_1_Connect_42_image_cdb_2ls_nrb" nd:nd-id="image_cdb_2ls_nrb" placement="inline" width="750"/></context>
<steps class="- topic/ol  task/steps ">
<step class="- topic/li     task/step ">
     <cmd class="- topic/ph     task/cmd ">Double-click on the guitar tuning app icon on your phone. </cmd>
     <info class="- topic/itemgroup     task/info ">I recommend using the Fender Tune app. Some tuning apps are even available online so you
                                                  just go to a website. However, because you will
                                                  tune your guitar most every time you pick it up to
                                                  play it, having the Fender Tune app on your phone
                                                  is adviseable.</info>
                                                  </step>
<step class="- topic/li     task/step ">
<cmd class="- topic/ph     task/cmd ">Place phone near where you will sit.</cmd>
</step>
<step class="- topic/li     task/step ">
<cmd class="- topic/ph     task/cmd ">Pick up guitar with left hand on neck. </cmd>
</step>
<step class="- topic/li     task/step ">
                                                  <cmd class="- topic/ph     task/cmd ">With your right hand, pick up your guitar
                                                  pick and hold it between your index finger and
                                                  your thumb.</cmd>
                                                  </step>
<step class="- topic/li     task/step ">
<cmd class="- topic/ph     task/cmd ">Sit down on a couch or chair.</cmd>
</step>
<step class="- topic/li     task/step ">
<cmd class="- topic/ph     task/cmd ">Put the guitar in playing position on left knee.</cmd>
</step>
<step class="- topic/li     task/step ">
                                                  <cmd class="- topic/ph     task/cmd ">Tune one string at a time starting with
                                                  string six (the thickest string).</cmd>
                                                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup     task/info "><image class="- topic/image " height="427" href="file:/Users/scottmcmahan/Desktop/techwritingsamples/guitar/guitarstrings2.jpg" id="unique_1_Connect_42_image_i4x_vks_nrb" nd:nd-id="image_i4x_vks_nrb" placement="inline" width="759"/></info>
                                                  <substeps class="- topic/ol     task/substeps " id="unique_1_Connect_42_tunesub" nd:nd-id="tunesub">
                                                  <substep class="- topic/li     task/substep " id="unique_1_Connect_42_check" nd:nd-id="check">
                                                  <cmd class="- topic/ph     task/cmd ">Check the pitch for that string against the
                                                  tuning app.</cmd>
                                                  </substep>
                                                  <substep class="- topic/li     task/substep " id="unique_1_Connect_42_low" nd:nd-id="low">
                                                  <cmd class="- topic/ph     task/cmd ">If the pitch is low, you need to tighten the
                                                  strings by turning the corresponding tuning
                                                  key.</cmd>
                                                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup     task/info ">The adage righty tighty, lefty loosy does
                                                  not always hold for guitar tuning. Tuning keys
                                                  that are right tighten the strings when the tuning
                                                  key is rotated clockwise. Those on the left side
                                                  of the headstock are tightened
                                                  counter-clockwise.</info>
                                                  </substep>
                                                  <substep class="- topic/li     task/substep " id="unique_1_Connect_42_high" nd:nd-id="high">
                                                  <cmd class="- topic/ph     task/cmd ">If the pitch is high, loosen the string by
                                                  turning the tuning keys clockwise for those on the
                                                  left of the headstock, and counter-clockwise for
                                                  those on the right.</cmd>
                                                  </substep>
                                                  <substep class="- topic/li     task/substep ">
                                                  <cmd class="- topic/ph     task/cmd ">Continue tuning each string with this
                                                  procedure until all six strings are tuned
                                                  properly.</cmd>
                                                  </substep>
                                                  </substeps>
                                                  <stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult ">Now, your guitar is in tune. You are
                                                  ready to play!</stepresult>
                                                  </step>
</steps>
</taskbody>
